    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="6"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d6">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conference 184.1—<persName>Buckler, W.
                        H</persName>.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Diplomatic Secretary, Commission to Negotiate Peace</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">to the Secretary-General, Commission to
                        Negotiate Peace</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJC1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In accordance with directions given orally by <persName corresp="#p_HCEMl"
                        >Colonel House</persName> last evening, January 8th, 7:00 P.M., I telephoned
                    to the Embassy in London to Mr. <persName>Butler Wright</persName>, Counsellor
                    of the Embassy, informing him that it was the desire of the President that Mr.
                        <persName>Buckler</persName>
                    <note n="4" xml:id="d6fn4">
                        <persName>William H. Buckler</persName>, special assistant in the Embassy in
                        Great Britain.</note> proceed at the earliest possible moment to Stockholm,
                    in conformity with the instructions given him during his recent visit to
                    Paris.</p>
                <p>I informed Mr. <persName>Wright</persName> of the desire of the Commissioners
                    that Mr. <persName>Buckler</persName> in leaving Sweden proceed either through
                    Germany or through Holland to Lausanne where he should arrive, if possible, by
                    the 20th instant.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">L. H.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
